57th Mage SotM <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwolfypaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfypaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/12/02 5:05:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=622.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mages</span><hr size=1> I really think it's about the pets.  Basically, chanters would rather be in groups without pets because eventually, the pets get us killed.  With a great player, it's rare, but still happens.  With a lousy player, it's frequent.<br>
<br>
There's a flip side to this -- the chanters avoid pet classes, so they also don't get good at dealing with pets.  I was in my upper 50s before I stopped fighting a pet that was on the wrong mob.  Eventually I learned -- if the pet is on the wrong mob, don't bother.<br>
<br>
Yes, I've seen the pet caster trying to back their pet off.  If I have grown to trust the individual player, I'll help.<br>
<br>
But that DOES increase the workload for the chanter.  It's a given -- even a good pet handler increases chanter workload.  Because the pet WILL end up on the wrong mob from time to time, and we have to do extra mes's or what-not.<br>
<br>
Also, from time to time, the pet holder will forget to back their pet before the current mob is about to die, and it goes and hits the mes'd mob before the tank can taunt it.  So the chanter gets hit a few more times.  If he's not expecting this, it can really toast the fight -- he probably does not have his back to a wall while he's starting a new round of mob-mesing.  So he gets interrupted a bunch of times and more mobs start to wake up.<br>
<br>
Let's say that your DPS is 10 percent better than a rogue.  To *me* you're not worth it, because you WILL increase my workload (guaranteed) and you MAY get my killed (frequency dependent on your own skills, which I may not know ahead of time if we don't play together).<br>
<br>
For a long time, I wouldn't add mages to my groups if I could avoid them.  Eventually, they got to the point where I'd add them *if* there weren't melee classes available.<br>
<br>
*tee hee*<br>
<br>
Maybe we need to implement a &quot;pet class certification test&quot;.  You play with one of the certification teams and you get a score from 0 to 100 based on your personal ability to play your pet.  You can then advertise your score when looking for a group.  Heck, we could POST the scores, too.<br>
<br>
*only half kidding*<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uugle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/12/02 9:59:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=622.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ugleduklin.tripod.com/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dscn0011s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mages</span><hr size=1> I haven't been playing my Casters much (Nec/Mage), but my group (mostly Guildies who hadn't seen me play them in forever) was pretty stoked in the Hole the other night, because with the two of us and our pets, we rocked.  We went AFK for a sec, and come back to group chat of &quot;get ready to evac&quot; because someone pulled, and more then one heh.  About 30 seconds after we got back, 4 or 5 MOB's that weren't dead had become so.  Between Earth pets being able to tank (and root and doing damage) and the Nec pet kicking butt, not to mention nukes, bad/over pulls generally weren't an issue.  At 41 (or even 51), Mage pets are great.  The problem becomes:<br>
<br>
Once MOB's are red-red to your pets, their damage goes way down.  While say a L51 cast Earth pet (around L42-43 con) will outdamage a L51 non-Monk/Rogue melee, a L56 cast Earth pet (maybe L47-48 con?), doesn't compare in damage to any 56 melee class.  Wizards nuke better then Mages do, no question.  Wizards can also snare, root, and evac/port.<br>
<br>
It really depends on group needs.  If a group has a War and Paladin already, do they need another tank?  Probably not.  In which case the pet, while doing a fair amount of damage, is a risk if you're in an area where crowd control or pathing is an issue.  The group is better off with a Wizard most likely.  If a group has a Shaman healer, which is better for them, a Druid who can nuke, SoW, heal, buff, etc., or a Mage?  If a group is fighting undead, the Necro 50% slow spell is going to help a group more then a Mage, not to mention some crowd control, etc.   <br>
<br>
Personally, until my Warrior hit 55, my Mage/Necro always had an easier time finding a group.  And if the place was packed or empty, they just killed stuff.  I've found that once people knew me in an area, I never had a problem getting into a group that had room for me.  And I keep my pets out all the time in Dungeons as long as I know the pathing.  Every once in a while they'll do something stupid, but I think we can all say we've done something silly before heh.  <br>
<br>
But, in your post I kind of get the impression that you started telling people how much more you contributed to a group then other classes.  That would be a bad idea if you did.  I always like it when I go somewhere and join a group, and stuff that was taking them two minutes to kill takes 30 seconds and they just go &quot;wow&quot;.  In a group with a taunter at 45+, you won't likely be outdamaging a decently equipped Rogue, definitely not in a long fight.  Your comment about &quot;your group would have died if.....&quot; just comes across wrong to me.  If they had a kick-tail Rogue, stuff would die fast.  If they had a Wizard with mana he's going to be able to burn through stuff with more DPS then you.  Telling people they are dumb not to take you because you are better then classX is just going to annoy people, and lessen your odds of getting a group.<br>
<br>
If you think Mages are underappreciated, I think Bards have it worse.  Bards make the melee kill SO much faster in a group.  Yet people insist on a Chanter for CC or a Shaman/Ench for hastes.  Sigh.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showMessageRange?topicID=622.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showMessageRange?topicID=622.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=622.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=622.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=622.topic&index=25><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/AddReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=622.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.threadControl?topicID=622.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=622.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=622.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub95.ezboard.com/BB